post_text:
La oficina de Participación Familiar de Título I y la Academia Familiar están encantados de ofrecer “Una serie de clases virtuales por las tardes impartido por la Academia Familiar de las Escuelas Públicas de Durham”. Estas clases virtuales apoyaran a las familias mientras hacemos la transición hacia el aprendizaje remoto en línea en nuestro distrito.

Canvas LMS es una plataforma de aprendizaje que admite el aprendizaje y la enseñanza en línea. Permite a los maestros publicar calificaciones, información de los padres y tareas en línea. Los padres aprenderán a configurar su cuenta como padres vigilantes/observador. Los padres podrán verificar las calificaciones ver fechas de vencimiento, leer instrucciones, ver anuncios, seguir calendarios y comunicarse con los maestros. Los padres tendrán la oportunidad de explorar la página de Canvas Discovery de DPS vaya a: https://canvas.dpsnc.net/ y descargue la aplicación de Canvas para padres en su dispositivo móvil para que puedan unirse como compañero en el aprendizaje de sus hijos.

Durham Public Schools has learned that the employee working at W.G. Pearson Elementary School who was previously identified as having a probable positive case of COVID-19 has in fact tested NEGATIVE for the virus. We have confirmed with the Durham County Department of Public Health that there are no individuals tested positive for COVID-19 at the DPS Learning Centers, including the one at W.G. Pearson, at this time.

The DPS Learning Center at W.G. Pearson Elementary will reopen on Wednesday, Sept. 2.

post_text: Heroes never die. Iconic and bigger than life, heroes live on through their work and through the people whose lives they’ve touched. Chadwick Boseman’s portrayal of the Black Panther/T’Challa is the role that made him an international star yet it was his display of community activism that showed that he was truly connected to it. His passion and talent is undeniable. His contribution to the Marvel Cinematic Universe will never be forgotten. His impact on our African-American youth, especially young black men, is immeasurable. We thank Boseman for giving us his all. We thank him for bringing to life a hero that we can truly call our own. He will be missed. #RIPChadwickBoseman #BlackPanther #Marvel

DPS families don't have to go it alone this year. Every student who needs a Chromebook or a hotspot for internet access will receive one through their school by the start of the school year. Our staff is hard at work to ensure you are supported. #WeAreDPS

Familias de las Escuelas Públicas de Durham no se sientan solas este año. Cada estudiante que necesite un Chromebook o dispositivo de internet inalámbrico recibirá uno a través de su escuela antes del inicio del año escolar. Nuestro personal está trabajando duro para asegurar que ustedes reciban apoyo. #SomosDPS

We are proud to launch the LEADurham Student & Teacher Fellowships. Students in grades 6-12 from across DPS have the opportunity to participate in this extracurricular independent study fellowship that will teach skills around Leadership, Equity, and Advocacy while helping our students build a platform to create the Durham they wish to see. | READ MORE: ignite.dpsnc.net/lead

¡Presentamos LeadDurham! El programa LEADurham es un estudio extracurricular independiente para aquellos interesados en profundizar su aprendizaje sobre la justicia social y el liderazgo comunitario. LEAD significa Liderazgo, Equidad, Abogacía y Durham. | leer más: https://bit.ly/DPSLeadDurhamES

ISLA NC was live.
July 14 at 7:00 PM ·

Por favor acompáñenos esta noche para una plática sobre la reapertura de las Escuelas Públicas de Durham con Superintendente Dr. Pascal Mubenga y Sub-Superintendente Dra. Nakia Hardy, Pablo Friedmann de las Escuelas Públicas de Durham, Juana Hernandez de la Fundación de Universidades de Carolina del Norte y Susana Benites Directora de Programas de ISLA.

Please join us tonight at 7pm for a conversation about the reopening of Durham Public Schools with Dr. Pascal Mubenga, the Superintendent of Durham Public Schools, Dr. Nakia Hardy, the Deputy Superintendent of Durham Public Schools, Pablo Friendmann from Durham Public Schools, Juana Hernandez from College Foundation of North Carolina and Susana Benites Program, Director of ISLA.

post_text:
Join us at 8 pm this evening for the premiere of "Litany" by Dasan Ahanu. This piece is dedicated to the resilient, powerful, and outspoken members of the #ClassOf2020.

Dasan Ahanu is a poet, emcee, writer, playwright, performance artist, lecturer, and educator Dasan Ahanu. Ahanu is also an alumni Nasir Jones Fellow, a resident artist at the St. Joseph's Historic Foundation/Hayti Heritage Center, Managing Director of Black Poetry Theatre, member of Black Jedi Zulus and Founder/Coordinator/Coach - Jambalaya Soul Slam/Bull City Slam Team.

"Litany" is inspired by Audre Lorde's "Litany for Survival."

Written by Dasan Ahanu
Produced by Truitt O'Neal

#DPSCommunity | Families with questions about new P-EBT food benefits from Durham County Social Services can call 2-1-1 or (888) 892-1162 (24 hours a day) should they have additional questions.

Individuals can apply for Food & Nutrition Services via Online (EPASS), paper application and mail back to Durham County Social Services, or by phone. DSS hours for assisting clients by phone are 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Monday thru Friday.
--
#ComunidadDPS | Las familias con preguntas sobre los nuevos beneficios alimenticios de P-EBT de los Servicios Sociales del Condado de Durham pueden llamar al 2-1-1 o al (888) 892-1162 (24 horas al día) si tienen preguntas adicionales.

Las personas pueden solicitar los Servicios de Alimentos y Nutrición a través de Internet (EPASS/Programa de Iniciativa para Servicios de apoyo analítico.), solicitud en papel y regresarlo por correo a los Servicios Sociales del Condado de Durham, o por teléfono. Las horas del Departamento de Servicios Sociales (DSS por sus siglas en inglés) para ayudar a los clientes por teléfono son de 9 a.m. a 1 p.m. de lunes a viernes.

SHARE/FORWARD: VOLUNTEERS NEEDED FOR DPS STUDENT/FAMILY MEAL DISTRIBUTION

Durham Public Schools, Durham County Government, the DPS Foundation and local nonprofits and restaurants have launched “Durham FEAST.” The program provides breakfast and lunch for children. Adults will receive shelf-stable food supplies and/or family-style casseroles. The program is free for EVERYONE.

The organization is in need of volunteers to help in this endeavor.

WEBSITE LINK: https://www.durhamfeast.org/volunteer
VOLUNTEER LINK: https://dpsfoundation.ivolunteer.com/durhamfeast

post_text:
The Durham Public Schools emergency meals program will continue, thanks to exceptions in the Mayor's stay-at-home order. Our sites will be open and providing take-home lunches and snacks. Please maintain a safe social distance from each other when you pick up your meals. We are happy to continue providing this service.

English | http://bit.ly/DPSMealsActivities2020

Continuará el programa de comidas de emergencia de las Escuelas Públicas de Durham, gracias a las excepciones en la orden de “Quedarse en Casa” por parte del alcalde. Nuestros sitios estarán abiertos y proporcionarán almuerzos y aperitivos (snacks) para llevar a casa. Por favor, mantenga una distancia social segura con las demás personas cuando recoja sus comidas. Estamos encantados de seguir prestando este servicio.

Español | bit.ly/2WA1wxK

Gabriela Maradiaga Panayotti, una pediatra en Durham; Dra. Viviana Martinez-Bianchi, una médica especialista en medicina familiar. Este Facebook Live será en español.

Please join us on Tuesday, March 24th at 7pm for a conversation about coronavirus (“Covid-19”) with Jenice Ramirez, Executive Director of ISLA; Pablo Friedmann from Durham Public Schools; Juana Hernandez from the College Foundation of North Carolina; Dr. Gabriela Maradiaga Panayotti, Dr. Gabriela Maradiaga Panayotti, Pediatrician in the Department of Pediatrics at Duke; and Dr. Viviana Martinez-Bianchi, a Family Medicine physician in the Duke Department of Family Medicine and Community Health. This Facebook Live will be in Spanish.
